User Story 1: Sign Up with Role Selection

As a new user,
I want to sign up with my email and select my role (Freelancer, Client, or Admin),
So that I can create an account appropriate to how I will use the platform.

Acceptance Criteria:
User must enter name, email, password, username.(3rd party verification)
User must select one role (Freelancer / Client / Admin).
Error messages shown for missing or invalid inputs.
Successful signup redirects to respective dashboard.




User Story 2: Sign In with Email and Password

As a registered user,
I want to log in using my email and password,
So that I can access my account and manage my work.

Acceptance Criteria:
Login form with email and password.
Error message for invalid credentials.
Successful login redirects to user-specific dashboard.
Option for “Remember Me” and “Forgot Password?”




User Story 3: Sign Up / Sign In Using Third-Party Identity Provider

As a user,
I want to sign up or log in using a third-party identity provider (e.g., Google),
So that I can quickly access the platform without creating a new account.

Acceptance Criteria:
"Sign in with Google" button.
Redirect to Google OAuth and back after authentication.
Automatically assign role or prompt for role on first sign-up.
Secure token handling.






User Story 4: Redirect Based on Role After Login

As a logged-in user,
I want to be redirected to a dashboard specific to my role (Freelancer, Client, Admin),
So that I only see features relevant to me.

Acceptance Criteria:
System detects role after login.
Freelancer goes to Freelancer Dashboard.
Client goes to Client Dashboard.
Admin goes to Admin Panel.ogin.
Freelancer goes to Freelancer Dashboard.
Client goes to Client Dashboard.
Admin goes to Admin Panel.
